statements: SELECT * FROM WindFarmLocations

SELECT id, name, location FROM WindFarmLocations ORDER BY name ASC

SELECT * FROM WindFarms;

SELECT Turbines.model_name, WindFarms.name FROM Turbines JOIN WindFarms ON Turbines.windfarm_id = WindFarms.id;

SELECT MaintenanceLogs.maintenance_date, MaintenanceLogs.description, Turbines.model_name, WindFarms.name FROM MaintenanceLogs JOIN Turbines ON MaintenanceLogs.turbine_id = Turbines.turbine_id JOIN WindFarms ON Turbines.windfarm_id = WindFarms.id;
SELECT WindFarms.name AS WindFarmName, COUNT(Turbines.turbine_id) AS TotalTurbines FROM WindFarms LEFT JOIN Turbines ON WindFarms.id = Turbines.windfarm_id GROUP BY WindFarms.name;

SELECT Turbines.model, MaintenanceLogs.maintenance_date, MaintenanceLogs.description FROM Turbines JOIN MaintenanceLogs ON Turbines.id = MaintenanceLogs.turbine_id WHERE Turbines.status = 'under_maintenance';

SELECT WindFarms.name, AVG(WeatherData.temperature) AS avg_temp, AVG(WeatherData.humidity) AS avg_humidity FROM WindFarms JOIN WeatherData ON WindFarms.id = WeatherData.wind_farm_id GROUP BY WindFarms.name;
